title: Missing Access-Control-Allow-Origin header for requests made to emergency alert endpoint
labels: [{'id': 366106217, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWwzNjYxMDYyMTc=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/microsoft/vscode/labels/*duplicate', 'name': '*duplicate', 'color': 'E2A1C2', 'default': False, 'description': 'Issue identified as a duplicate of another issue(s)'}]
body:
https://github.com/microsoft/vscode/blob/main/src/vs/workbench/contrib/emergencyAlert/electron-sandbox/emergencyAlert.contribution.ts sends request from the workbench which has origin `vscode-file://vscode-app` that fails due to missing response headers.

```
Access to fetch at 'https://main.vscode-cdn.net/core/insiders.json' from origin 'vscode-file://vscode-app' has been blocked by
CORS policy: No 'Access-Control-Allow-Origin' header is present on the requested resource. If an opaque response serves your
needs, set the request's mode to 'no-cors' to fetch the resource with CORS disabled.
```

title: build: add npmrc to remote/web folder
body:
`remote/web` takes the configuration from root when run via postinstall step, but if a user were to `cd remote/web` and run `npm i` then system configuration will be applied.

Addressed accidental change via https://github.com/microsoft/vscode/commit/31e1cb3e716cf2b0579ebb6c6f723ba9b3717662

FYI @Tyriar

body:
* Backports https://github.com/electron/electron/pull/43774/commits/0f45d14a9a9cf22627451319a7e6d7f44bb3fea8 to support telemetry for utility process, refs https://github.com/microsoft/vscode/issues/202385

Fixes https://github.com/microsoft/vscode/issues/213780
